## Comprehensive Report: Image Generation Model Implementation in Vercel AI SDK

Based on my thorough exploration of the Vercel AI SDK codebase, here's the complete architecture for image generation models:

---

### 1. INTERFACE SPECIFICATION

The current image model interface is **ImageModelV3** (with legacy v2 also present). Here are the key interface definitions:

#### **ImageModelV3 Interface** (`packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3.ts`)

```typescript
export type ImageModelV3 = {
  /**
   * Must specify interface version for backwards compatibility
   */
  readonly specificationVersion: 'v3';

  /**
   * Provider name for logging (e.g., "openai.image", "google.image")
   */
  readonly provider: string;

  /**
   * Provider-specific model ID (e.g., "dall-e-3", "imagen-3")
   */
  readonly modelId: string;

  /**
   * Max images per single API call - can be:
   * - Fixed number
   * - undefined (use global limit)
   * - Function returning async number
   */
  readonly maxImagesPerCall: number | undefined | GetMaxImagesPerCallFunction;

  /**
   * Main generation method
   */
  doGenerate(options: ImageModelV3CallOptions): PromiseLike<{
    /**
     * Generated images as base64 strings or Uint8Array binary data.
     * Return in native format from API (no unnecessary conversions)
     */
    images: Array<string> | Array<Uint8Array>;

    /**
     * Array of warnings about unsupported features or compatibility modes
     */
    warnings: Array<SharedV3Warning>;

    /**
     * Provider-specific metadata - keyed by provider name
     * Example: { "openai": { "images": [{ revisedPrompt: "..." }] } }
     */
    providerMetadata?: ImageModelV3ProviderMetadata;

    /**
     * Response metadata for telemetry
     */
    response: {
      timestamp: Date;
      modelId: string;
      headers: Record<string, string> | undefined;
    };

    /**
     * Optional token usage info
     */
    usage?: ImageModelV3Usage;
  }>;
};
```

#### **ImageModelV3CallOptions** (`packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3-call-options.ts`)

```typescript
export type ImageModelV3CallOptions = {
  /**
   * Text prompt for generation (can be undefined for upscaling)
   */
  prompt: string | undefined;

  /**
   * Number of images to generate
   */
  n: number;

  /**
   * Image size - format: "{width}x{height}" (e.g., "1024x1024")
   * undefined uses provider default
   */
  size: `${number}x${number}` | undefined;

  /**
   * Aspect ratio - format: "{width}:{height}" (e.g., "16:9")
   * undefined uses provider default
   */
  aspectRatio: `${number}:${number}` | undefined;

  /**
   * Seed for reproducible generation
   * undefined uses provider default
   */
  seed: number | undefined;

  /**
   * Input images for editing or variation generation
   * Can be base64 strings or binary data
   */
  files: ImageModelV3File[] | undefined;

  /**
   * Mask image for inpainting operations
   * Indicates areas to modify (transparency indicates regions to edit)
   */
  mask: ImageModelV3File | undefined;

  /**
   * Provider-specific options passed as API body parameters
   * Keyed by provider name: { "openai": { "style": "vivid" } }
   */
  providerOptions: SharedV3ProviderOptions;

  /**
   * Abort signal for cancellation
   */
  abortSignal?: AbortSignal;

  /**
   * Custom HTTP headers for the request
   */
  headers?: Record<string, string | undefined>;
};
```

#### **ImageModelV3File** (`packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3-file.ts`)

```typescript
export type ImageModelV3File =
  | {
      type: 'file';
      mediaType: string; // IANA media type (e.g., "image/png")
      data: string | Uint8Array; // base64 string or binary
